Base.Explanation: Check if a variable exists in the session variable list. The variable is specified by its name. The action returns a boolean variable with the result.

ArrayElement.Name: Variable name
ArrayElement.Description: The name of the variable to be checked for existence in the session variable list (example: %SessionId%).

ArrayElement.Name: Variable exists flag
ArrayElement.Description: The name of the variable used to return the result. The variable is generated automatically, only the name needs to be specified (example: %VariableExsistFlag%).

Base.Explanation: Copy a variable from the session variable list. Both the name and value of the variable are copied. If the variable already exists in the project variable list, the value is overwritten.

ArrayElement.Name: Variable name
ArrayElement.Description: The name of the variable to be copied from the session variable list to the project variable list (example: %ConnectionString%).

Base.Explanation: Copy a variable to the session variable list. Both the name and value of the variable are copied. If the variable already exists in the session variable list, the value is overwritten.

ArrayElement.Name: Variable name
ArrayElement.Description: The name of the variable to be copied from the project variable list to the session variable list (example: %ConnectionString%).
